ed by another.\n\n- Michelle\n|\nI was no longer afraid. Not of important men, not of trustees and such; for knowing now that there was nothing which I could expect from them, there was no reason to be afraid.\n\n- Ralph Ellison, Invisible Man\n|\nAll teachings are mere references. The true experience is living your own life. Then, even the holiest of words are only words.\n\n- Ming-Dao\n|\nOnce you learn to quit, it becomes a habit.\n\n- Vince\n|\nWe write to taste life twice, in the moment and in retrospect.\n\n- Anaïs\n|\nMy heart is small, like a love of buttons or black pepper.\n\n- S. Jane Sloat, In the Voice of a Minor Saint\n|\nI was supposed to write a romantic comedy, but my characters broke up.\n\n- Ann Brashares, The Second Summer of the Sisterhood\n|\nWe can become inspired to shape a higher, more ideal future, and when we do, miracles happen.\n\n- James Redfield, The Tenth Insight: Holding the Vision\n|\nPeople aren't either wicked or noble. They're like chef's salads, with good things and bad things chopped and mixed together in a vinaigrette of confusion and conflict.\n\n- Lemony Snicket, The Grim Grotto\n|\nHappiness does not come from without, it comes from within\n\n- Helen\n|\nThere is no truth,' Stephanie said mysterously. 'Only perspectives.\n\n- Michelle Hodkin, The Evolution of Mara Dyer\n|\nAt the age of four, you were an artist. And at seven, you were a poet.\n\n- Seth Godin, Linchpin: Are You Indispensable?\n|\nUsing your talent, hobby or profession in a way that makes you contribute with something good to this world is truly the way to go.\n\n- Simon Zingerman, We All Need Heroes: Stories of the Brave and Foolish\n|\nIf I wanted you to understand, I would explain it better.\n\n- Johan\n|\nThere were only the great diamonds and sapphires and emerald mists and velvet inks of space, with God's voice mingling among the crystal fires.\n\n- Ray Bradbury, The Illustrated Man\n|\nIf your thoughts are higher than your problems, you can fly above them.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nGod created everyone uniquely and for a purpose, and not to be on this earth as a passive spectator\n\n- Sunday\n|\nYou learn almost as much about a thinker from what he reads—in particular, what he likes and what he disdains—as from what he writes himself.\n\n- Rodney\n|\nA true professional not only follows but loves the processes, policies and principles set by his profession.\n\n- Amit Kalantri, Wealth of Words\n|\nUnfortunately, our society is a victim of such a world system which does not encourage people to live consciously and become who they were called to be\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWe left you there, lonely,Beauty your power,Wisdom your watchman,To hold the clay tower.from 'The Tale of the Tiger Tree\n\n- Vachel\n|\nWhen life gets too hard on you just forget everything,be yourself and move on\n\n- Suhagini\n|\nThe person may have a scar, but it also means they have a story\n\n- Jodi Picoult, The Storyteller\n|\nJesus Christ is three in one: the way, the truth, and the life.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nThe way your curious eyes were chasing mine when I stood in front of you, I knew I had known these eyes before.\n\n- Khadija Rupa, Unexpressed Feelings\n|\nRien ne va arrêter ma quête pour te trouver' No one will stop my quest to find you.\n\n- Susane Colasanti, Something Like Fate\n|\nProfound hearts, wise minds, take life as God makes it; it is a long trial, and unintelligible preparation for the unknown destiny.\n\n- Victor Hugo, Les Misérables\n|\nThe gift of knowledge is empowering, but the gift of wisdom is life-changing.\n\n- A.D.\n|\nWhen you catch yourself slipping into a pool of negativity, notice how it derives from nothing other than resistance to the current situation.\n\n- Donna Quesada, Buddha in the Classroom: Zen Wisdom to Inspire Teachers\n|\nReason Develops Passion, Passion Creates Motivation, Motivation is the driving force behind all actions = GREAT RESULTS.\n\n- Ray Mancini, Zen, Meditation & the Art of Shooting: Performance Edge - Sports Edition\n|\nStay with your passion but have a philosophy that is beyond your strength so that you can have a legacy, even a legacy that will outlast you.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nWhen I hug you, I feel like I am hugging the universe of joy, and I emerge with the ecstasy of life.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nRemember this, - where there is life there is hope. You're alive. Embrace this, because YOU CAN DO ANYTHING while there is breath in your body.\n\n- Lola Jaye, By The Time You Read This\n|\nA poet is a man who manages, in a lifetime of standing out in thunderstorms, to be struck by lightning five or six times.\n\n- Randall\n|\nI said that I had heard curiosity could be harmful, in particular to cats\n\n- Michael Chabon, Moonglow\n|\nOne thing guaranteed in life is that you’ll experience twists and turns, obstacles, roadblocks, and battles.\n\n- Mensah\n|\nMuscle breakdowns are important for muscle growth and similarly, Life breakdowns are important for quantum Life growth\n\n- Harrish\n|\nSometimes exhaustion is not a result of too much time spent on something, but of knowing that in its place, no time is spent on something else.\n\n- Joyce\n|\nIf you believe our cause so hopeless, why join us?''Because you offered something I had forgotten could be offered, a choice. And I choose to die free.\n\n- Anthony  Ryan, Queen of Fire\n|\nLife seemed to him to be a narrow cage, and her iron bars were many and dense, and there was only one way out.\n\n- Leonid\n|\nIn all of living, have much fun and laughter. Life is to be enjoyed, not just endured.\n\n- Gordon\n|\nHappiness is based on a just discrimination of what is necessary, what is neither necessary nor destructive, and what is destructive\n\n- Ursula K. Le Guin, The Ones Who Walk Away from Omelas\n|\nYou must build and develop a greater force on the inside of you, in this way, you will be able to speak and stand against ungodliness and injustice in the land.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of 